      "writtenOn": "2018-02-15T07:25:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, but I also allow this error because for some devices (in the future), the width can be 49. For example, if the device scale factor is 3.875, then floor((floor(50 * 3.875) + 0.501)/3.875) \u003d\u003d 49.\n\nIf we test this on only existing devices, then I guess the exact 50 is fine. How do you think of it?",
